<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7970c9d6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1269"><num value="1269">§ 1269.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7970c9d7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1269/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authority</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority to promulgate regulations for the efficient enforcement of this chapter, except as otherwise provided in this section, is vested in the Commission.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7970c9d8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1269/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Joint regulations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Treasury and the Commission shall jointly prescribe regulations for the efficient enforcement of the provisions of <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s1273">section 1273 of this title</ref>, except as otherwise provided therein. Such regulations shall be promulgated in such manner and take effect at such time, after due notice, as the Commission shall determine.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7970c9d9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/86/613/s10">Pub. L. 86–613, § 10</ref>, <date date="1960-07-12">July 12, 1960</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/74/378">74 Stat. 378</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/314/tII/s204/b/4/B">Pub. L. 110–314, title II, § 204(b)(4)(B)</ref>, (E), <date date="2008-08-14">Aug. 14, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/3041">122 Stat. 3041</ref>, 3042.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7970c9da-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
